ws" class="cs-google-link" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" role="img" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">I had a sprinkler emergency and David came out immediately; found an effective solution to get me through until the major repairs could be made; and took care to make sure my house wasn't without water in the meantime. I am so grateful for his kindness and professionalism. He demonstrated considerable expertise and decisive decision making that got me through this emergencies with minimal stress. He is trustworthy and will be the first one I'll call on any future sprinkler needs.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Jennifer Wees-Schkade</span> <span class="cs-role">2 years ago</span></div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113879630740524577871/reviews" class="cs-google-link" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" role="img" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">Brainard’s Greenscapes is a top notch business. I have called on them on several occasions to fix issues with my irrigation system and for new projects. David, the owner, is a sincere, honest individual, who cares about his business and his customers. His employees are also kind and always professional. They are punctual and complete the job as promised and clean up after they are done. I am very pleased with David and his company and have recommended him to my neighbor, who is also a widow because I know he is honest and will not take advantage of her. David is a good guy and I recommend that you give him a call and see for yourself.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">George Rodriguez</span> <span class="cs-role">6 years ago</span></div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113926776793747685994/reviews" class="cs-google-link" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li></ul></div></section><section id="faq-506"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> FAQ</span><h2 class="cs-title">Artificial Turf FAQs</h2></div><ul class="cs-faq-list"><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How much does artificial turf installation cost in Las Cruces?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Artificial turf installation in Las Cruces typically runs $8 to $20 per square foot installed, all-in. Pet-grade turf, premium drainage backings, putting-green nylon, and stone or concrete edging push you toward the high end. Standard backyard projects with a quality landscape-grade turf and silica-sand infill come in around $10 to $14 per square foot. Most residential installs we do fall between $3,000 and $25,000 total. The on-site estimate is always free.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How long does artificial turf last in the New Mexico desert sun?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>A quality landscape-grade turf installed correctly will last 15 to 20 years in Las Cruces, even with our intense UV. The turfs we install carry UV-stabilization warranties from the manufacturer (typically 10 to 15 years against fading and fiber breakdown). The two things that shorten lifespan are bad base prep and cheap turf. We use a properly compacted base, the right infill weight, and turf rated for high-UV climates.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Is artificial turf safe and comfortable for dogs?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Yes. Pet-grade artificial turf has a perforated drainage backing that lets urine pass straight through, plus an antimicrobial infill (zeolite or similar) that captures ammonia and stops smell from building up. We rinse the turf with the existing hose bib once a week as part of the install plan. Dogs take to it immediately, no muddy paw prints, no dead urine spots, no digging. We install pet-grade turf for dog runs, side yards, and full backyards across Las Cruces.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Does artificial turf get hot in summer?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Yes, in direct sun on a 100°F afternoon, turf surface temperature can run 30 to 50 degrees above ambient air temperature. The fix is shade, infill choice, and a quick hose-down. We recommend a cooling infill (zeolite or a coated sand) on full-sun installs and pair it with a shade structure or strategic tree placement for any space where kids or pets will be barefoot at peak heat. Morning, evening, and shaded turf stays comfortable year-round.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How do you clean and maintain artificial turf?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Maintenance is light. Rinse with a hose every week or two to clear dust and pet waste. Brush the fibers up with a stiff-bristle push broom every few months to keep the blades vertical. Pull weeds out of the perimeter (rare with proper edging and weed barrier). Plan on adding a top-up of infill every five to seven years. Compared to a real lawn, you'll save on water, mowing, edging, fertilizer, and weed killer. Most clients spend less than 15 minutes a month on it.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">What is artificial turf made of?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Modern artificial turf is a polyethylene or polypropylene fiber tufted into a perforated polyurethane or polyolefin backing, then filled with infill (silica sand, coated sand, zeolite, or a rubber blend, depending on use). The good stuff is UV-stabilized, lead-free, and rated for residential traffic. We only install turf from manufacturers with documented warranties and verified safety testing. We can show you product spec sheets at the consultation so you know exactly what's going in your yard.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Will artificial turf comply with the Las Cruces water ordinance?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Yes, and it actually sidesteps the ordinance entirely for the area you cover. Artificial turf needs no irrigation, so you don't have address-parity watering days, no Monday lockout, and no April 1 to September 30 daytime watering window to manage. Many homeowners pair turf with a drip-irrigated planting border to keep curb appeal high while cutting outdoor water use 80% or more. We'll walk you through the Las Cruces Water Conservation Program at the consultation.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How long does an artificial turf install take?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Most residential artificial turf installs take three to five days on-site. Day one is removal of existing grass or rock and grading. Day two is base prep, compaction, and weed barrier. Day three is rolling out the turf, seaming, anchoring, and infilling. Day four is brushing, final cleanup, and walkthrough. Larger or full-property projects, or installs that include a putting green or hardscape edging, run a week or more. We give you the full schedule before any work starts.</p></div></details></li></ul></div></section><section id="services-related-184"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Beyond Turf</span><h2 class="cs-title">More Services in Las Cruces</h2><p class="cs-text">Artificial turf pairs naturally with the rest of what we install. Same in-house crews. Same workmanship guarantee.</p></div><ul class="cs-related-list"><li class="cs-related-card"><a href="/services/landscaping/sod-installation/" class="cs-related-link"><h3 class="cs-related-title">Sod Installation</h3><p class="cs-related-text">Live grass option for shaded areas or yards where real lawn is the right call.</p><span class="cs-related-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></span></a></li><li class="cs-related-card"><a href="/services/landscaping/xeriscaping/" class="cs-related-link"><h3 class="cs-related-title">Xeriscaping</h3><p class="cs-related-text">Drought-tolerant native landscapes that pair beautifully with a small turf inset.</p><span class="cs-related-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></span></a></li><li class="cs-related-card"><a href="/services/hardscaping/" class="cs-related-link"><h3 class="cs-related-title">Hardscaping</h3><p class="cs-related-text">Patios, walkways, retaining walls, and stone borders that frame the new turf.</p><span class="cs-related-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></span></a></li><li class="cs-related-card"><a href="/services/irrigation/drip-irrigation/" class="cs-related-link"><h3 class="cs-related-title">Drip Irrigation</h3><p class="cs-related-text">Drip-fed planting borders around the turf so the yard reads green without the water bill.</p><span class="cs-related-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></span></a></li><li class="cs-related-card"><a href="/services/landscape-maintenance/" class="cs-related-link"><h3 class="cs-related-title">Landscape Maintenance</h3><p class="cs-related-text">Seasonal turf brushing, infill top-ups, and surrounding planting upkeep on a schedule.</p><span class="cs-related-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></span></a></li></ul></div></section><section id="lets-talk-318"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-tree.svg" height="457" width="427" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-tree"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-1.svg" height="20" width="64" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-1"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-2.svg" height="15" width="56" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-2"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-3.svg" height="15" width="46" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-3"><div class="cs-container"><h2 class="cs-title">Ready to Stop Watering the Lawn?</h2><a href="/contact/" class="cs-talk-button">Schedule Free Estimate</a></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-grass-top.svg" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-grass"></section>
